Package dbms.parser

Class Summary
SQLParser This class implements a Parser for SQL-92.It doesn't yet support the "not equal" operator as well as the '(' & ')' that alter the priority of the operations.
SQLPatterns This class describes every lexical unit our system can recognise by assigning a regular expression to it.
SQLSymbols This class assigns all the symbols our system needs to recognise and handle, with a keyword.
 

Enum Summary
SQLReserved This enumeration type contains all the reserved words that the user of our DBMS system can use to make his SQl queries.
SQLTokens This enumeration type contains the tokens that our DBMS system's parser produces, when reading a file or a user's command with SQL statements and recognises appropriate lexical units.
